content:
# UF Google Trends Analysis

## What "uf" refers to
- Primarily University of Florida (most common interpretation)
- The Florida Gators are the defending 2025 NCAA Men's Basketball national champions
- Currently ranked #19, with 13-5 record (4-1 SEC), atop SEC standings

## Key Events in Feb 2-10 Window
- Feb 2 (Monday): No major UF events - just a regular weekday
- Feb 7 (Saturday, 7:30 PM): UF basketball at Texas A&M
- Feb 10 (Tuesday): UF basketball at Georgia

## Current State
- Current interest value: 49 (as of Feb 1, 2026)
- Resolution threshold: ±3 points

## Factors to Consider
1. Basketball game on Feb 10 could spike searches (game day effect)
2. As defending champions, interest in Gators remains elevated
3. No major games on Feb 2 for comparison baseline
4. Google Trends has inherent sampling variability
5. Weekday vs weekday comparison (Mon vs Tue) - similar patterns expected
6. Campus utility disruption mentioned in news could drive some searches

## Base Rate Considerations
- For a ±3 threshold on value of ~49 (6% variation allowed)
- Regular university search terms are relatively stable
- Sports events can cause temporary spikes but typically modest
